.\" Manpage for ddl.
.TH DDL 1 "May 4, 2026" "v0.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ddl \- Dedalo: A strongly opinionated C++ build system

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ddl
[\fICOMMAND\fR] [\fIARGUMENTS_FOR_BUILD_CPP\fR]

.SH DESCRIPTION
Dedalo is a strongly opinionated C++ build system that allows you to describe, configure, and build C++ projects using only a single \fBbuild.cpp\fR config file and a C++ compiler with support for at least C++20. No scripting, data, or domain specific languages required.

.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-version
Prints the version number.

.TP
.B init
Creates the \fBbuild.cpp\fR file and the directory structure in the current directory, using the current directory name as the project name.

.TP
.B build [\fITARGET_NAME\fR]
Builds the specified target. If no \fITARGET_NAME\fR is provided, builds the project's default target.

.TP
.B run [\fITARGET_NAME\fR]
Builds and immediately runs the specified target. If no \fITARGET_NAME\fR is provided, builds and runs the project's default target.

.TP
.B clean
Deletes the \fB./build\fR directory.

.TP
.B test
Builds and runs the testing target. Note: This command is currently unimplemented.

.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Creating a new project
.nf
$ mkdir my_project
$ cd my_project
$ ddl init
$ ddl run
.fi

This generates the following directory structure, builds, and runs the project, which prints "Hello, World!".

